Section 1:
Act 746 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: S4/7/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 SENATE BILL 627
4
5 By: Senators Irvin, J. Bryant
6 By: Representatives Wooldridge, Cozart, McGrew, Andrews
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO ASSIST THE ADMINISTRATION OF THE CODE
10 ENFORCEMENT SECTION OF THE DEPARTMENT OF LABOR AND
11 LICENSING; TO REPEAL THE ELECTRICAL CONTRACTOR AND
12 AIR CONDITIONING ELECTRICIAN LICENSES; TO TRANSFER
13 AND UPGRADE THE CLASS C HVACR LICENSE; TO IMPROVE THE
14 LICENSING OF APPRENTICE ELECTRICIANS; TO HELP THE
15 ELEVATOR OWNERS SATISFY TESTING REQUIREMENTS; TO
16 CLARIFY ANNUAL LICENSING RENEWAL PERIODS; TO AID IN
17 THE ADMINISTRATION OF THE STATE’S ELECTRICIAN, HVACR,
18 ELEVATOR, AND BOILER SAFETY LAWS; AND FOR OTHER
19 PURPOSES.
20
21
Subtitle
22
23 TO ASSIST THE ADMINISTRATION OF THE CODE
24 ENFORCEMENT SECTION OF THE DEPARTMENT OF
25 LABOR AND LICENSING AND THE STATE'S
26 ELECTRICIAN, HVACR, ELEVATOR, AND BOILER
27 SAFETY LAWS.
28
29 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
30
31 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 17-28-101(1), concerning the definition of
32 air conditioning electrician, is repealed.
33 (1) “Air conditioning electrician” means an individual who is
34 limited to a license classification possessing the necessary qualifications,
35 training, and technical knowledge for the installation, maintenance, and
36 extension of electrical conductors and equipment solely for the purpose of
