36 or his or her authorized representatives representative may at any time
21 04-07-2025 15:06:51 LGL199

As Engrossed: S4/7/25 SB627
1 suspend an inspection certificate when in their his or her opinion the boiler
2 or unfired pressure vessel for which it was issued cannot be operated without
3 menace to the public safety or when the boiler or unfired pressure vessel is
4 found not to comply with the rules provided in this subchapter.
5 (2) Any insurance company inspector or inspection service
6 provider who has been issued an Arkansas commission and is inspecting boilers
7 or pressure vessels in this state shall have corresponding powers with
8 respect to operating certificates for boilers or pressure vessels insured by
9 the company employing him or her.
10 (3) The suspension of an operating certificate shall continue in
11 effect until the boiler or pressure vessel shall have been made to conform to
12 the rules of the Boiler Inspection Division Section and until the operating
13 certificate shall have been reinstated.
14 (b) Any inspector of the division Boiler Inspection Section or any
15 commissioned inspector of any insurance company or inspection service
16 provider who after inspection of a boiler or unfired pressure vessel shall
17 find it unsafe for operation shall suspend its certificate of inspection and
18 forbid its further use until it shall have been made to conform to the
19 standards adopted by the division Boiler Inspection Section and until its
20 certificate of inspection shall have been reinstated by an authorized
21 inspector.
